The paper presents a deep convolutional neural network for multi-view stereo reconstruction, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with 3D reconstruction, which falls under the graphics (GR) sub-category. The use of pre-training and feature activations suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (LG) sub-category. The paper involves processing of images and aggregation of information, which may fall under the robotics (RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (AI) sub-category.
